- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on translating code between human languages. 
- cs.ED (Education) is also likely as the paper discusses the educational utility of the translation tool. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to develop the translation tool. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to develop the translation tool. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the study of public code repositories on GitHub to inform translation decisions.
